sentence: T. V. Sankaranarayanan (Tiruvalangadu Vembu Iyer Sankaranarayanan, born 7 March 1945) is a Carnatic vocalist (South Indian classical singer), known for his music that stems from the style of his guru and maternal-uncle, Madurai Mani Iyer.
His father, Vembu Iyer, was a disciple of Madurai Mani Iyer; and his mother was Mani Iyer's sister.
At the age of nine, he started learning music from his uncle (maamaa), Madurai Mani Iyer.
